 (1,1,'Action and Adventure','The stories under this genre usually show an event \nor a series of events that happen outside the course\n of the protagonistâ€™s ordinary life. \nThe plot is mostly accompanied by danger and \nphysical action. These stories almost always move \nquickly and the high pace of the plot is usually an\n important part of the story.',0),
 (2,1,'Anthology','An anthology is a collection of series of works such \nas short stories, poems, essays, plays, etc. by \ndifferent authors into a single volume for publication. \nThe selection of such works is made based on \nsome common theme or subject of books and \nusually done by an editor or small editorial board.',0),
 (3,1,'Classic','Classic refers to the fictions that are accepted as the \nmost important and influential books of a particular\n time period or place. These books are widely taught \nin schools.',0),
 (4,1,'Comic and Graphic Novel','These books are based on a sequence of \nhand-drawn pictures. The story is usually told \nvisually with very few words and those words are \nmostly placed either in panels on top or bottom of \npictures or as speech bubbles.',0),
 (5,1,'Crime and Detective','As the name suggests, this book genre deals with \ncrime, criminal motives and the investigation and \ndetection of the crime and criminals.',0),
 (6,1,'Drama','Dramas are stories composed in verse or prose, \nusually for theatrical performance, where conflicts \nand emotions are expressed through dialogue and \nactions.',0),
 (7,1,'Fable','Fables are fictional narratives in prose or verse that \ntypically features personified animals, mythical and \nlegendary creatures, plants, etc. as the main \ncharacters.  (8,1,'Fairy Tale','Fairy tale is usually a story for children that involves \nimaginary creatures and magical events.',0),
 (9,1,'Fan-fiction','Fan Fiction, as the name suggests, is a fiction \nwritten by a fan of a particular book or book series. \nThe characters and the plot of fan fiction are usually \ntaken from the original work but the story is different.\n',0),
 (10,1,'Fantasy','A Book under this genre contains a story set in a \nfantasy world â€“ a world that is not real and often\n includes magic, magical creatures, and \nsupernatural events.',0),
 (11,1,'Historical Fiction','Historical fiction is a genre of book that includes \nwritings that reconstruct the past.  (12,1,'Horror','Horror is a genre that is intended to or has the \nability to create the feeling of fear, repulsion, \nfright or terror in the readers. In other words, it \ncreates a frightening and horror atmosphere.',0),
 (13,1,'Humor','Humor fiction is usually full of fun, fancy, and \nexcitement. It is meant to entertain and sometimes \ncause intended laughter in readers.',0),
 (14,1,'Legend','Itâ€™s a story, sometimes of a national or folk hero that \nis considered to be based on facts but also includes \nimaginative material.  (15,1,'Magical Realism','It is a genre of book wherein magical or unreal \nelements play a natural part in an otherwise-realistic \nenvironment.',0),
 (16,1,'Mystery','Mystery books have a suspenseful plot that often \ninvolves a mysterious crime. Suspects and motives \nare considered and clues throughout the story lead \nto a solution to the problem.',0),
 (17,1,'Mythology','These books include a legend or traditional narrative,\n often based in part on historical events, that reveals \nhuman behavior and natural phenomena by its \nsymbolism and often pertaining to the actions of the\ngods.',0),
 (18,1,'Realistic Fiction','Realistic fiction has a story that is true to life and seem\ns real but isnâ€™t actually real. Stories under this book \ngenre are often set in modern times and have \ncharacters who seem like real people.',0),
 (19,1,'Romance','The primary focus of romance fiction is on the \nrelationship and romantic love between two people. \nThese books have an emotionally satisfying and \noptimistic ending.',0),
 (20,1,'Satire','Satire is a genre of book that entertains making fun \nof vices, foolishness, shortcomings, etc. of \nindividuals, corporations, government, or \nsociety through sarcasm and irony. It is often done \nwith the intention of inducing the sense of \nimprovement among people.',0),
 (21,1,'Science Fiction (Sci-Fi)','Science Fiction typically deals with imaginative and \nfuturistic concepts such as advanced science and \ntechnology, time travel, extraterrestrial life, etc. The \nstories are often set in the future or on other planets.\n',0),
 (22,1,'Short Story','A short story is a short prose fiction that typically can \nbe read in one sitting. The stories under this genre \noften do not have subplots. It deals with a few \ncharacters and aims at the unity of effect and often \nconcentrate on the creation of mood rather than plot.',0),
 (23,1,'Suspense/Thriller','This genre of book is characterized and defined by \nthe moods they evoke among the readers, giving \nthem heightened feelings of suspense, excitement, \nthrill, surprise, anticipation, and anxiety. Literary \ndevices such as plot twists and cliffhangers are \nextensively used in this genre.',0),
 (24,2,'Biography/Autobiography','Biography is a narrative on someoneâ€™s life written by \nsomeone else. When a person himself writes about \nhis life, then the book is called an autobiography.',0),
 (25,2,'Essay','An essay is usually a short literary composition that \nreflects an authorâ€™s outlook or point of view on a \nparticular topic.',0),
 (26,2,'Memoir','A memoir is basically a collection of memories that \nan individual writes on moments or events that he \nexperiences in his life. These writings are taken to \nbe factual.',0),
 (27,2,'Narrative Nonfiction','Narrative nonfiction (also known as literary \nnonfiction or creative nonfiction) is a genre of books\n that uses literary styles and techniques to create \nfactually accurate narratives in a format that tells a \nstory.',0),
 (28,2,'Periodicals','Periodicals as the name suggest, are written \nperiodically at regular definitive intervals. \nNewspapers, magazines, Journals are some \nexamples.',0),
 (29,2,'Reference Books','These are books that we refer to when we need \nsome specific information. Some examples of this \ngenre of books are a dictionary, an encyclopedia, an \natlas, etc.',0),
 (30,2,'Self-help Book','Self-help books contain information that is intended \nto help the readers to solve their personal problems \nand make their life better.',0),
 (31,2,'Speech','This is a public address or discourse written into a \nbook.',0),
 (32,2,'Textbook','A textbook is a manual of instruction in any branch \nof study. It contains an authoritative and detailed \nfactual description of a topic.  (33,2,'Poetry','Poetry is one of the most important genres of books \nin which the expression of feelings and ideas is \ngiven intensity by the use of distinctive style and \nrhythm. Poems written under poetry can be of \ndifferent types according to the style in which they \nare written.',0),
